01/06/2003
IVAILOVGRAD, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov insisted on Saturday (31 May) Bulgaria has the political and social will needed to combat organised crime. Talking to journalists, he commented on the outcome of his meeting earlier in the week with officials from the interior ministry and special forces. "What remains to be done is to translate good ideas into successful practice," Parvanov said.
In other news, Bulgaria and Turkey signed an agreement Friday for the real-time exchange of information to prevent illegal migration and human and drug trafficking. The protocol was part of a broader agreement on coast guard co-operation. (BTA, Mediapool, Standart - 31/05/03; Anadolu Agency, BTA - 30/05/03)
